 TONGLIAO, Nov. 12 (Xinhua) -- Tongliao City in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region has been walloped by the strongest snowstorm ever recorded. In response to the record blizzard, Tongliao government has carried out snow removing operations round-the-clock to resume local transportation. As of Thursday evening, the traffic in Tongliao was basically unblocked.  Aerial photo shows vehicles transporting snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  A forklift shovels snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/En Hao)  A forklift shovels snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  A forklift shovels snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  Aerial photo shows vehicles removing snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  A forklift shovels snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  Aerial photo shows vehicles removing snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)  Aerial photo shows a forklift shoveling snow from the road in Tongliao, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 11, 2021. (Xinhua/Lian Zhen)■ Produced by Xinhua Global Service■  